commit.message: Initial Commit
Drop support for Python 3.4: update readme.
Drop support for Python 3.4 which is not supported by Django 2.1.
Fixed minimal requirement changed by error.
Added support for Django 2.1.
Fixed error when generating qr code from lazy text (#1)
Upgrade requirements.
Add date for release of version 1.0.

Use proper casing for Pillow library.
Remove old auto-generated manifest file.

Added ability to use a `QRCodeOptions` instance with `options` keyword argument in all tags.
Added tests for this feature.
Update demo application and readme file.
Removed obsolete test when building qrcode.QRCode()
Increase test coverage.

Escape colon char (':') if it appears within a contact detail or a wifi configuration.
Add a second terminal semi-colon at the end of the text representing a wifi configuration, as recommended in some sources.
Exclude handling of the situation where Pillow is not available from test coverage.
Increase test coverage.
First attempt at integrating code coverage with coverall.io

Refactor code in serve.get_url_protection_options().
Refactor code of demo app.

Bump version number to 1.0.
Refactor some code.
Improved examples in demo app, documentation and tests.

Added support for `coordinates` keyword argument to `qr_for_geolocation`, `qr_for_google_maps`, `qr_url_for_geolocation`, and `qr_url_for_google_maps`:
* Added tests for new feature.
* Update demo app with new feature.
* Update documentation with new feature.
Update change log.
Update changelog.
